<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>Select the <b class="Bold">Enable Training</b> checkbox to enable the training videos by role code. Select this checkbox and go to the <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Organization Configuration/Groups/Training.htm" target="_blank" alt="Training">Training</MadCap:xref> tab in Groups to select the available training videos to make available in FireLight. Users can click the <b class="Bold">Training</b> button on the FireLight navigation bar and click a training video to view, or they can click the <b class="Bold">View All Videos</b> link to choose from all available training videos for FireLight. When the user is within an activity for which training videos are available, e.g., signing process, the navigation bar includes a Training button that the user can click to access training videos for that feature. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online">See also <MadCap:xref href="../../../../UserGuide/Training/Training.htm" target="_blank" alt="Training [User Instructions]">Training [User Instructions]</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></body>
</html>